Holidays are not everywhere.
In Hungary, holidays are precisely stipulated by law and it has become a common practice to move working days around holidays, which is less likely to happen next year.
Neither in the United States nor in the European Union there is a common holiday.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and national holidays and days of rest.
Working days are mostly associated with church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is a work holiday - in the New Year already so that people can rest after New Year's Eve.
During the year there are 11 free holidays.
The national holiday is March 15, celebrating the revolution of 1848, and October 23, commemorating the revolution of 1956.
On the 20th of August we celebrate the founding of the state, on the 1st of May work, on the 1st and 2nd of November we commemorate the deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, we have two days of Easter, Summer and Christmas holidays.
Since our national, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend according to the calendar, it has become a practice to move the working day in cases where we would only work one day before or after a holiday.
The price for prolonged weekends is, of course, that we stay at work and at school on the previous Saturdays.
When the day immediately preceding or following the holiday is worked, the Minister of Labour has been regulating in a special decree for many years.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and workers employed by them, to public servants and to persons in public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or operate even during days of rest.
This year, there will be a change in the working rules only around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, because according to previous experience, most people will "work" in advance the days between Christmas and New Year's Eve or take advantage of the saved holiday.
In the coming year, several of our holidays fall in the middle, respectively, at the end of the week, so the shifts of the working day will be less than this year.
For the first time, the calendar is turned around a work holiday, so that then workers can stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday 26 April will be a working day, so Friday 2 May can be a day of rest.
The next move is related to the holiday of 23 October: on Saturday, 18 October, it will work instead of Friday, 24.
At the end of the year, however, next year will be able to take place entirely in the sign of holidays, because from December 24, they will have almost everywhere nonstop holidays even though New Year's Eve falls on Wednesday.
