State debt is the debt of the central government and is generated primarily by the cumulative deficits of the state budget.
Government debt is financed by treasury vouchers, government bonds, direct loans or, for example, loans from the European Investment Bank.
Internal debt has so far increased this year by 38.5 billion to SEK 719.4 billion.
The foreign debt of the state this year has so far increased by SEK 1.7 billion to SEK 123.3 billion.
