The tools he used, namely a mini hockey clothed with an insulator to prevent an electrical shock on solar panels producing several hundred volts, were invented and "written out" by astronauts on board the station.
After the operation ended, Scott Parazynski waited until the panel was completely disassembled and then invented his tools and returned to the inside of the station.
