Which insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident, represents a considerable expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of holding a driver’s license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive an agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking care of paying damages in the event of an insurance event.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, status, gender, length of holding a driver’s license, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the greater the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that married people have fewer accidents than self-employed drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of rides, and thus the likelihood of an accident.
With increased frequency, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the premium price.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose such insurance that best corresponds to his profile of the insured.
We will show you the most important variable for choosing this or that type of insurance, which in addition to meeting the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five encounter various disadvantages such as low driving experience and short driving license holdings when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discounted premiums in order to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"The part of the insurance event payment that the client will provide will be predetermined when determining the premium price, which will be the higher the lower the participation would be," explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in traffic so that the client insures against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
The Recommendation .
If you are under twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is an increase in the basic rate.
“Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After the limit of twenty-five years, it is easier for drivers to contract insurance because the customer’s risk index is reduced, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to contract insurance against all risks with a discount.
“Young people usually can’t take advantage of previously acquired experience when an accident occurs, or even when driving,” the director of the European company in Spain assures, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the “fear of the newcomer” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation permits.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their rates will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discounted premium (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants in the traffic, starting the third year from the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their driving is quieter and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford the luxury to get the highest discount,” says Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended insurance against all risks with a discounted premium (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would most suit us given our personal situation.
