In order to acquire competing Freenet, the companies jointly established a joint venture for SMEs.
On Thursday, United Internet announced that the two companies would satisfy themselves with more than a 10% stake in Freenet for now and would not use their right to take over another 18.49% of the enterprise.
It is considered that companies remain open to all options, in particular the possibility of further increasing their share in Freenet AG.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership were concluded in mid-November.
This months-long and hardly transparent game about Freenet is part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million mobile contract customers and 1.27 million customers with complete or DSL connection.
Holding United Internet and Drillische so far held a 6,01% stake in Freenet.
Now it has been agreed that Drillisch will get approximately another 4%.
The right to buy 18.49% of Vatas was agreed in August.
